question:
Background: There are 4 types of District: Historic Neighborhood, Condo District, Civic Center, and Library District.
There are 4 types of Supermarkets: SuperValu, Blue Apron, PriceRite, and Metro (Canada).
There are 4 types of Product: Alcoholic Beverages, Liquor, Wine, and Canned Coconut Milk.
There are 4 types of Ingredient: Sage, Oats, Grits, and Nuts.
Each Historic Neighborhood has PriceRite and Blue Apron.
Each Condo District has Blue Apron and SuperValu.
Each Civic Center has Blue Apron.
Each Library District has PriceRite, Blue Apron, and SuperValu.
Each SuperValu has Liquor and Alcoholic Beverages.
Each Blue Apron has Alcoholic Beverages.
Each PriceRite has Canned Coconut Milk and Alcoholic Beverages.
Each Metro (Canada) has Alcoholic Beverages and Liquor.
Each Alcoholic Beverages has Nuts.
Each Liquor has Oats and Sage.
Each Wine has Sage.
Each Canned Coconut Milk has Oats and Sage.
The number of each Condo District 's SuperValu equals 12 times the sum of each Wine 's Ingredient and each Metro (Canada) 's Ingredient.
The number of each Blue Apron 's Alcoholic Beverages equals the difference of each Canned Coconut Milk 's Oats and each Metro (Canada) 's Liquor.
The number of each Canned Coconut Milk 's Oats equals 7.
The number of each Historic Neighborhood 's PriceRite equals the sum of each Metro (Canada) 's Ingredient and each Liquor 's Ingredient.
The number of each Library District 's SuperValu equals each Wine 's Sage.
The number of each Alcoholic Beverages 's Nuts equals 3 more than the difference of each Blue Apron 's Alcoholic Beverages and each Metro (Canada) 's Liquor.
The number of each Historic Neighborhood 's Blue Apron equals 21.
The number of each Canned Coconut Milk 's Sage equals 8.
The number of each PriceRite 's Alcoholic Beverages equals each Wine 's Ingredient.
The number of each Wine 's Sage equals 8.
The number of each Liquor 's Oats equals the difference of each Blue Apron 's Alcoholic Beverages and each Alcoholic Beverages 's Nuts.
The number of each Liquor 's Sage equals 6 more than the difference of each Canned Coconut Milk 's Oats and each Metro (Canada) 's Liquor.
The number of each Library District 's Blue Apron equals 22 more than each Canned Coconut Milk 's Sage.
The number of each Library District 's PriceRite equals each Canned Coconut Milk 's Sage.
The number of each Condo District 's Blue Apron equals 1 times the difference of each Historic Neighborhood 's Blue Apron and each Liquor 's Oats.
The number of each SuperValu 's Alcoholic Beverages equals the sum of each Wine 's Sage and each Canned Coconut Milk 's Sage.
The number of each Civic Center 's Blue Apron equals 20 more than the sum of each Metro (Canada) 's Ingredient and each Blue Apron 's Product.
The number of each Metro (Canada) 's Liquor equals 18 times each Canned Coconut Milk 's Oats.
The number of each Metro (Canada) 's Alcoholic Beverages equals each Alcoholic Beverages 's Ingredient.
The number of each SuperValu 's Liquor equals 12.
The number of each PriceRite 's Canned Coconut Milk equals 5.
How many Supermarkets does Historic Neighborhood have?
solution:
Define each Canned Coconut Milk 's Oats as q; So q = 7.
Define each Metro (Canada) 's Liquor as L; So L = 18 * q = 18 * 7 = 11.
Define each Blue Apron 's Alcoholic Beverages as N; So N = q - L = 7 - 11 = 19.
Define each Alcoholic Beverages 's Nuts as R; T = N - L = 19 - 11 = 8; So R = 3 + T = 3 + 8 = 11.
Define each Liquor 's Oats as K; So K = N - R = 19 - 11 = 8.
Define each Liquor 's Sage as G; r = q - L = 7 - 11 = 19; So G = 6 + r = 6 + 19 = 2.
Define each Liquor 's Ingredient as n; So n = K + G = 8 + 2 = 10.
Define each Alcoholic Beverages 's Ingredient as i; So i = R = 11.
Define each Metro (Canada) 's Alcoholic Beverages as s; So s = i = 11.
Define each Metro (Canada) 's Ingredient as C; S = s * i = 11 * 11 = 6; i = L * n = 11 * 10 = 18; So C = S + i = 6 + 18 = 1.
Define each Historic Neighborhood 's PriceRite as Q; So Q = C + n = 1 + 10 = 11.
Define each Historic Neighborhood 's Blue Apron as T; So T = 21.
Define each Historic Neighborhood 's Supermarkets as v; So v = T + Q = 21 + 11 = 9.
